00:59:24,534 --> 00:59:28,715
For a tight mix, for me, one of the most important things is tonal elements.

1162
00:59:29,936 --> 00:59:32,898
So if there's a tonal element that's happening in the game,

1163
00:59:33,398 --> 00:59:37,062
it's very important that that is in a similar key, or same key, or same root note,

1164
00:59:37,082 --> 00:59:39,444
or whatever it might be, of the music that's playing.

1165
00:59:39,464 --> 00:59:42,987
So you'll notice in a couple of levels there you pick up a chaingun, right?

1166
00:59:43,307 --> 00:59:46,469
And this chaingun is able to be split out into three chainguns.

1167
00:59:46,489 --> 00:59:49,072
So you've got like this ultimate killer chaingun thing going on, right?

1168
00:59:49,172 --> 00:59:49,672
Yeah, the turret.

1169
00:59:49,872 --> 00:59:51,853
And the sound of this chain gun,

1170
00:59:53,054 --> 00:59:55,135
the bullets firing out of it happening so quickly

1171
00:59:55,175 --> 00:59:56,336
that it produces a tone.

1172
00:59:56,636 --> 00:59:58,077
That was the philosophy behind that.

1173
00:59:58,578 --> 01:00:01,499
Now we made sure that the tone of that was a D note.

1174
01:00:01,639 --> 01:00:02,680
It was a low D note.

1175
01:00:02,760 --> 01:00:05,101
And that D note was sitting with the same music

1176
01:00:05,121 --> 01:00:06,202
that was sitting in the background,

1177
01:00:06,222 --> 01:00:07,683
which is also sitting on a D.

1178
01:00:08,624 --> 01:00:11,426
So when you do that, you get this really solid mix that's happening.

1179
01:00:11,446 --> 01:00:13,007
You don't have frequencies that are clashing.

1180
01:00:14,008 --> 01:00:18,953
My best thing that I can say about that really is that it's something that really needs to be considered on every project.

1181
01:00:19,033 --> 01:00:25,018
It's not an afterthought, and it's not something that you can fix in Wwise or whatever you're using later on.

1182
01:00:25,599 --> 01:00:30,363
If you're ducking stuff when something else happens, or if you're trying to compress this when this is happening,

1183
01:00:30,663 --> 01:00:33,445
you're fixing a problem that shouldn't be there in the first place.

1184
01:00:34,166 --> 01:00:38,729
Now those tools exist to allow us to fix that, but ultimately if you can carve your sounds

1185
01:00:38,769 --> 01:00:41,851
and your music with that stuff in mind to begin with, you're going to end up with a

1186
01:00:41,891 --> 01:00:43,892
